/10/ten-t-corridors_en.htm</span></a></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">A more detailed map of Core Corridor 8 is </span><span style="background-color:#ffff00; font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">attached</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn5"></a><a href="#_ftnref5">[5]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> </span><a href="http://www.theyworkforyou.com/wrans/?id=2010-01-12d.309628.h&amp;s=%28WCML%29+1935-10-01..2013-11-14+section%3Awrans#g309628.r0"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.theyworkforyou.com/wrans/?id=2010-01-12d.309628.h&amp;s=%28WCML%29+1935-10-01..2013-11-14+section%3Awrans#g309628.r0</span></a></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn6"></a><a href="#_ftnref6">[6]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> </span><a href="http://tentea.ec.europa.eu/en/ten-t_projects/30_priority_projects/priority_project_14/"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">http://tentea.ec.europa.eu/en/ten-t_projects/30_priority_projects/priority_project_14/</span></a></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn7"></a><a href="#_ftnref7">[7]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> Connecting Europe Facility (CEF) funds</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn8"></a><a href="#_ftnref8">[8]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> </span><a href="http://ec.europa.eu/transport/themes/infrastructure/ten-t-policy/review/doc/com_sec(2011)0101_en.pdf"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">http://ec.europa.eu/transport/themes/infrastructure/ten-t- policy/review/doc/com _sec(2011)0101_en.pdf</span></a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">   (p9) “</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">public interest should lead to a continuous communication that imp</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">lies a true involvement and would avoid the problems described.”</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn9"></a><a href="#_ftnref9">[9]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> It seems clear from discussions on the various media that many commentators assume that the UK will be in full control over all of these decisions in relation to HS2. That is less self-evident since the latest agreement in the European Parliament. </span></p></body></html>